Imagery Description: (a) Draped woman seated between standing draped woman, with phiale and fillet, and nude youth with fillet and stick, (b) nude youth with wreath and seated draped woman, holding phiale and spray. The lid is bellNon Sepcifiedshaped, decorated with red bands and rows of white dots, with a black knob. It may well not belong to this particular vase—cf. the lid illustrated in Patroni, fig. 75, 9.
